# React Components

## Component Structure
- Use functional components exclusively (no class components)
- Export named components: `export function UserProfile() {}` (not default exports)
- Define Props type inline or as `interface UserProfileProps {}`
- Destructure props in the function signature

## TypeScript
- Define explicit prop types — never use `any`
- Use `React.ReactNode` for children, `React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>` for handlers
- Prefer `interface` over `type` for component props (extendable)
- Use `as const` for literal unions and configuration objects

## Patterns
- Keep components under 100 lines; extract sub-components when larger
- Co-locate related files: `UserProfile.tsx`, `UserProfile.test.tsx`, `UserProfile.module.css`
- Use early returns for conditional rendering instead of nested ternaries
- Move complex logic to custom hooks, keep components as thin rendering layers

## Performance
- Wrap expensive computations in `useMemo`
- Wrap callback props in `useCallback` when passing to memoized children
- Use `React.memo()` only when profiling shows re-render bottlenecks
- Avoid creating objects/arrays in render — hoist static values

## Styling
- Prefer CSS Modules or Tailwind over inline styles
- Use semantic class names that describe purpose, not appearance
